<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Questions and Answers from March 31st</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>How many &quot;middle strength&quot; spells (spells that a player will use on a daily basis, when fighting a monster) can a player cast before he/she runs out of mana?</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Horizons does not currently use mana, so the answer would be either zero or infinite. Spells have a casting time and a recovery time. During the recovery time, other spells may be cast (assuming they are available) but the original spell cannot. Whether we apply mana to the system or not will be determined during Beta 2.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Will joining certain prestige schools unlock unique and powerful spells for mages, or will it only improve their ability in that particular circle?</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Some prestige schools that include magic-based skills grant new magical abilities to followers of the school. Naturally, progressing in these schools also results in an increase in the skills associated to the school, thus increasing the effectiveness of any spells cast that depend upon that particular skill.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Is leveling required to change schools, or can I simply change when I choose to?</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
You can change from one school to a different school by interacting with the appropriate master of the school. If you meet the prerequisites for membership within the new school, you will be accepted. Leveling is not related in any way to school affiliation, other than some schools have skill requirements for entry.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Will there be any form of channeling? For example, the tornado spell you showed. Will the mage simply say a few words, wave his/her hands and boom there's a tornado or, Will the mage have to actually concentrate to keep it spinning, and will we be able to see the tornado begin as a small cyclone and form an actual tornado or will a huge tornado appear from no where?</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Some spells do require that the caster maintain focus for the duration of the spell; if the caster switches to a different action, the spell ends. All spells require a target to be cast, whether it is the caster, another player character, an NPC, an object or a monster. Some spells have an area of effect outside of the target, which results in effects being applied to nearby valid targets in addition to the focus target of the spell. None of the current spells allow the caster to guide the path of a spell after it is cast.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Is there a lot of variety in the actual spells themselves, or is it just a lot of &quot;fireball 1&quot; which is nearly identical to &quot;iceball 1&quot;, which each do slightly less damage than &quot;fireball 2&quot;, but otherwise they function almost identically?</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Each type of magic has it’s own flavor, so there are a variety of effects associated with a type of magic. Fire tends to do more damage than ice, but ice includes additional effects that fire doesn’t have, for example.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Can a PC cast spells--- in armor? While wielding weapons? If you switch to a fighter school?</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
A character who has sufficient knowledge to cast a spell (represented by possession of the spell in their spell book) can cast that spell unless that specific spell is prohibited due to: insufficient skill for that type of spell, equipment which blocks magic, insufficient time has passed for them to recover from last casting the spell, or the spell is school specific. All of these are unique to the spell and vary from school to school and spell to spell. So, some spells can be cast while wearing armor, some spells may be cast while wielding weapons, and some spells can be cast while no longer a member of a magic studying school.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>On dragon magic. Will there be different colored dragon for each circle of magic that they are best at or will a dragon be able to choose the circle they like?</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Players will be able to choose the appearance of their dragons based upon their personal preferences. We are not imposing a limited appearance system onto dragons, especially since they are already limited in the equipment that they have available to them.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>How will players get the majority of their spells? Through crafting, questing or looting scrolls?</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
The majority of spells will come from players that craft spell scrolls. Many of the original spells will be discovered through quests or adventure. The ability to cast these spells will be earned through experience, questing, and adventure.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Will there be spells to mesmerize, stun, or root opponents, or area effect versions of such spells, thus making players with these abilities all-powerful and necessary in groups, turning combat with multiple enemies into a joke, and turning PvP (if implemented) into an affair in which your entire group is immobilized by a single spellcasting opponent and then killed one by one!?</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
We are not going to allow the experience you describe to occur in Horizons, but there will be spells and abilities that result in modifications in the ability to move and or conduct combat. There will be counters to these spells and abilities and the balancing to avoid the described situation is already underway.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>How will Horizons' magic system be different than the magic systems of other games? Specifically, how will it differ from the Healer/Buffer, Nuker, Pet caster, Crowd Control caster templates that many other MMORPGs all seem to use (i.e. EQ, DAoC, AO, AC2, SB)?</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
That will be largely up to the individual player to decide. Since we allow players to change their schools, players will be able to mix and match their “templates” as they wish to create new roles in the game. We will be offering many of the “templates” you sited, because they represent basic roles that players will want. We will also be offering other choices, though.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>We have been told that spells will have 'sockets' that will allow one to put 'runes' in them thus 'tweaking' the spell and altering some of it function. My question then is, can you give us a rough number of runes that exist? What will these runes do to the spell, generally? Increase range? Put in a bit of extra damage?</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
We follow the same procedure for runes, techniques, spells, weapons, races and everything else in our game. We create the system and then begin to add the content. The systems are designed to be modular and extensible. Today, there are only a dozen described runes; tomorrow there will be more. By launch there will be many more with others to follow. Just as today we have only four official races, we know that by launch there will be more. We have a very specific idea of how many more, but we are not announcing that number until it has been reached. Yes, runes provide varying tweaks to the resultant spell. They include: damage modification, damage type modification, range modification, target modification, recovery modification, visual effect modification, auditory modification and behavioral modification.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Can I wield a weapon or another item in my hands and cast a spell or do I need a special Item (wand, Spellbook) to cast?</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Your spell book does not need to be in your hand (nor can it be) in order to cast. Some spells can be cast while wielding a weapon or carrying other items, while others cannot. Magic is channeled through the character; it comes from the world and is directed by the knowledge of the caster through their body. Some magic has been contained within objects through the efforts of characters. There are also specific items in the world (such as wands) that benefit the caster and allow them to more carefully focus the power of magic.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>How many specialty schools are there for mages? How many can a mage be in at once?</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
There are currently four prestige schools that study the use of magic. It is only possible to be in one adventure school at any one time. This is true not just for those that study magic, but also those that study the physical arts. It is possible to simultaneously participate in a crafting school.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>How does the Artifact system affect magic using players?</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Of the many possible Artifacts that can be constructed by player communities, there are several that provide a benefit specifically to casters of magic. Current examples include increased skill for all affected, greater speed in recovery from casting, increased range, increased scope, and longer duration. <br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <p><HR SIZE=2 WIDTH="100%">
